```markdown
#Active recon
#(Directly interacts with target systems or network)
shodan host 8.8.8.8 (retrieves live info about a specific IP from Shodan, may involve scanning depending on Shodan’s last scan but from your perspective it’s querying live data of the IP)

eyewitness --web -f urls.txt -d ./reports/ (actively connects to each URL and takes screenshots)

theharvester (can be active or passive depending on flags, but often uses active queries like DNS bruteforce if enabled)

amass (can be active if run with active scanning options)

recon-ng (can be active if modules do direct scanning; depends on modules used)
